18.body: My Infrastructure as Code is based on Terraform . All the files are publicly available on GitHub .
18.title: As Code

19.body:
./forge
├── ansible # Ansible configuration, pre-deployment
├── hosts # Hosts configuration
│ ├── common # Common configuration for all hosts
│ ├── exegol
│ ├── eadu
│ └── scariff
├── stacks # Stacks of services
│ ├── admin

│ ├── monitoring
│ ├── media

├── hosts.tf # Hosts configuration

├── providers.tf

24.body: MeTube is a web interface for youtube-dl . It's a simple downloader for YouTube videos and playlists.

25.body: Paste your URL on the homepage, choose your format/quality and click on the download button. The download will start automatically. 6.body: To deploy the /forge infrastructure, you will need: Ansible Terraform Git This three tools must be installed on your local machine. The installation process installs the following tools on the remote machine: Docker Docker Compose Git zsh
6.title: Local Configuration

7.body: The configuration is tested only for Debian, I can't guarantee that it will work on other distributions. There are few requirements for the remote hosts: All the hosts must have the same user with root privileges. All the IPs address must be written in the ansible/hosts.yml file. All the hosts must have SSH keys and the host machine must have the public key.
7.title: Host Configuration

8.body: On the host machine, clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/Xavier2p/infra-as-code.git && cd infra-as-code
8.title: Clone repository
